Lucas Glover, Thomas Bjorn Share One-Shot Lead in British Open 2nd Round

-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 
2011-07-15T09:38:15Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-15/merkel-fails-to-evoke-kohl-as-biggest-german-boom-brings-no-political-gain.html
American Lucas Glover and Denmark’s
 Thomas Bjorn  share a one-shot lead at 5-under par in the second
round of the British Open.  Glover is 1-under through nine holes today at Royal St.
George’s in Sandwich, England, while Bjorn tees off at 12:26
p.m. local time. English amateur Tom Lewis, who was tied for the
lead with Bjorn after the first round, made a bogey at the par-4
fourth hole to fall to 4-under.  American Webb Simpson and  Spain ’s Miguel Angel Jimenez are
also 4-under. Simpson has made two pars and Jimenez tees off at
1:10 p.m.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  